			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know its a bit late for new changes for the upcoming set, but here are some changes I'd like to see :
<br />

<br />
1) Cap the score boost given for large numbers of ships of a given SIZE. Say only the first 10k ships of a given size add to score (or less, certainly no more: 10k gunboats = 1/4 mill score), any more have no effect.
<br />

<br />
Reason : stops abusive fluffing while allowing sensible use of fluffing to hide weakness, etc... Abusive flufing is that done ONLY by members of the top council or those NAPed with them, where a player fluffs out of range of all attacks at 1/2hr to 1hr+s fluff range of any other player to rebuild. As the tactic is only available to the top + allies, it spoils the game for those who aren't / won't ally with the top and is abusive.
<br />

<br />
2) Give a hefty survival bonus to commies on defence and a hefty penalty to the attacker.
<br />

<br />
Reason : It makes sense (don't have to go far to recover a commie in your own system) and it helps mid range players get decent commies. I spent all last set before hols in high mid range.... every time I got over 500 dooms, I was hit by 720+ dooms from the top players. Apart from it being nigh impossible to win those battles (and If I did, a second armada hit me within 20mins), it was virtually impossible to get decent commies as most of them died despite escape pods. The attacker already has all the advantages, and the current (reasonable) survival bonus for winning makes it easy for the top to keep decent commies and damn hard for the middle to keep them.
<br />

<br />
3) Tweak ship scores, as per my previous suggestion : 
<br />
<a href="http://www.archspace.org/board/viewtopic.php?t=1029" target="_blank">http://www.archspace.org/board/viewtopic.php?t=1029</a>
<br />

<br />
Reason: 'cos of score, after teched up, only dooms (+ fodder/rapers) are worth building... Tweaking scores would make others worthwhile, but dooms still the best if you can get to a full armada of them.
<br />

<br />
4) [the hardest to implement] Make rebuiling faster after being hit. On every defence, for every ship killed (attacker or defender), 0-100% (say (2D6 - 2) x 10) ) "ship carcasses" of that class should become available to the defender. If he builds ships of that class, they should cost 50% of the normal PP and use up 1 of those carcasses for each ship. This would allow for double speed rebuilding after being hit and defleeted.
<br />

<br />
Reason : If you get hit, you lose all your ships, which can be a really hard blow to recover from. This makes it easier... but only for the defender !
<br />

<br />
==============
<br />
OK, flame them !  <img src="images/smiles/icon_evil.gif" alt="Evil or Very Mad" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
