				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I see the problem with a single % roll... making devices etc. worthwhile and still not letting survival go over 100%.
<br />
Currently: lvl-20 + EP + no racial and loss = 60% losses which sucks.
<br />

<br />
How about splitting it into two rolls : one to survive the battle, one to get picked up alive, and making EP/HB worth 10% each : 
<br />

<br />
Survive Battle = 25 + Lvl x 2 + EP + racial + 10% on victory
<br />
 so 55% to 95%, if EP=+10 and racial goes -10 thro' +10.
<br />

<br />
Get picked up = 30 + Lvl x 2 + HB + 20% if defender
<br />
 so 70% to 100% if survive battle.
<br />

<br />
(I presume targoid clones have a separate roll anyway to clone)
<br />
Providing one of the rolls cannot get to 100%, then there'd always be some deaths.
<br />

<br />
Hmmm... not sure maths works... But you shouldn't need both devices to get a decent survival rate (75%+ = decent... 85% would be nice) and you should still lose some with both devices.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
