				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">yeah, 40% losses... 60% survival. It still sucks !
<br />
OK, someone else come up with a decent formula, where all the bonuses make a real difference, yet where 100% survival doesn't happen.
<br />

<br />
Maybe we should be calculating a % chance to die (or per 1000), with some bonuses giving multipliers to that chance.
<br />

<br />
Say 60 - 2 x level = % chance of dying (=58 to 20%)
<br />
Devices, racial mods etc are multipliers to that %
<br />
Twice the current values would work :
<br />
Bosalian, lvl-20 with EP and HB and victory =
<br />
20% x 0.80 x 0.60 x 0.60 x0.60 = 3.5 % chance of loss
<br />

<br />
Teca, lvl-20 with EP and loss =
<br />
20% x 0.60 = 12%... I could live with that.
<br />

<br />
Agerus, lvl-20 with EP and win =
<br />
20% x 1.2 x 0.60 x 0.60 = 8.6 % chance of loss... could you live with that Cyph ?
<br />

<br />
And a bonus for defender too would be nice.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
